{"downloaded": true, "htmlmade": false, "id": "32367113", "source": "MED", "pmid": "32367113", "pmcid": "PMC7198318", "fullTextIdList": {"fullTextId": "PMC7198318"}, "doi": "10.1093/databa/baaa022", "title": "Why data citation isn't working, and what to do about it.", "authorString": "Buneman P, Christie G, Davies JA, Dimitrellou R, Harding SD, Pawson AJ, Sharman JL, Wu Y.", "authorList": {"author": [{"fullName": "Buneman P", "firstName": "Peter", "lastName": "Buneman", "initials": "P", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "School of Informatics, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Christie G", "firstName": "Greig", "lastName": "Christie", "initials": "G", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Information Services, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Davies JA", "firstName": "Jamie A", "lastName": "Davies", "initials": "JA", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Centre for Discovery Brain Sciences, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Dimitrellou R", "firstName": "Roza", "lastName": "Dimitrellou", "initials": "R", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Information Services, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Harding SD", "firstName": "Simon D", "lastName": "Harding", "initials": "SD", "authorId": {"@type": "ORCID", "#text": "0000-0002-9262-8318"}, "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Centre for Discovery Brain Sciences, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Pawson AJ", "firstName": "Adam J", "lastName": "Pawson", "initials": "AJ", "authorId": {"@type": "ORCID", "#text": "0000-0003-2280-845X"}, "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Centre for Discovery Brain Sciences, University of Edinburgh."}}}, {"fullName": "Sharman JL", "firstName": "Joanna L", "lastName": "Sharman", "initials": "JL", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Novo Nordisk Research Centre Oxford, Novo Nordisk Ltd. Department of Computer and Information Science, University of Pennsylvania."}}}, {"fullName": "Wu Y", "firstName": "Yinjun", "lastName": "Wu", "initials": "Y", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Novo Nordisk Research Centre Oxford, Novo Nordisk Ltd. Department of Computer and Information Science, University of Pennsylvania."}}}]}, "authorIdList": {"authorId": [{"@type": "ORCID", "#text": "0000-0002-9262-8318"}, {"@type": "ORCID", "#text": "0000-0003-2280-845X"}]}, "dataLinksTagsList": {"dataLinkstag": "altmetrics"}, "journalInfo": {"volume": "2020", "journalIssueId": "2900917", "dateOfPublication": "2020 Jan", "monthOfPublication": "1", "yearOfPublication": "2020", "printPublicationDate": "2020-01-01", "journal": {"title": "Database : the journal of biological databases and curation", "ISOAbbreviation": "Database (Oxford)", "medlineAbbreviation": "Database (Oxford)", "NLMid": "101517697", "ISSN": "1758-0463", "ESSN": "1758-0463"}}, "pubYear": "2020", "pageInfo": "baaa022", "abstractText": "We describe a system that automatically generates from a curated database a collection of short conventional publications-citation summaries-that describe the contents of various components of the database. The purpose of these summaries is to ensure that the contributors to the database receive appropriate credit through the currently used measures such as h-indexes. Moreover, these summaries also serve to give credit to publications and people that are cited by the database. In doing this, we need to deal with granularity-how many summaries should be generated to represent effectively the contributions to a database? We also need to deal with evolution-for how long can a given summary serve as an appropriate reference when the database is evolving? We describe a journal specifically tailored to contain these citation summaries. We also briefly discuss the limitation